# Karadakh, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Karadakh (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Korodinsky Selsoviet, Gunibsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 390 as of 2010.
Geography
Karadakh is located 32&nbsp;km northwest of Gunib (the district's administrative centre) by road, on the Avarksoye Koysu River. Uzdalroso and Koroda are the nearest rural localities.
